Document step-1/step-2 any-GitHub-model verification

Two independent proofs landed this session:

1. qwen3-coder-plus autonomously fixed vq_bet/policy_server.py line 36
   (from gpt import -> from vq_behavior_transformer.gpt import) via a
   clean read_file -> edit_file -> validate loop on first try, with zero
   loop-breaker intercepts needed for the primary fix. Proves weak LLMs
   can drive source-level repairs end-to-end.

2. Claude onboarded tonyzhaozh/act from zero: analyze_repo -> read_file
   policy.py + imitate_episodes.py -> write_file a minimal BasePolicy
   adapter with _validate_only=True shortcut -> setup_env -> validate
   mode=smoke. Final result: SMOKE_OK: infer(no-image) returned actions
   of len=14. ACT uses policy(qpos, image) as its inference pattern,
   which does NOT match any of the 6 wrap_policy regex patterns — so
   this is the first real "any GitHub model" demonstration.

Also documents the honest model caveats we hit during the qwen-max and
qwen3-coder-plus runs: both weak models have base64 emission defects on
long payloads (write_file is stressful, edit_file is fine). The
infrastructure is model-agnostic, but prefer Claude Sonnet/Opus or
GPT-4o for the write_file step.

